# Prisma & Database Conventions

## Migrations (REQUIRED)

**Every database schema change MUST have a corresponding SQL migration file AND a down migration.**

- Migration files live in `backend-ts/prisma/migrations/`
- Name format: `<descriptive_name>.sql` + `<descriptive_name>.down.sql`
- Use `ALTER TABLE ... ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS` for additive changes
- Use `IF NOT EXISTS` / `IF EXISTS` guards so migrations are idempotent
- After writing the migration SQL, update `prisma/schema.prisma` to match, then run `npx prisma generate`
- NEVER use `prisma db push` or `prisma migrate dev` — those are not used in this project

### Commands

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `npm run migrate:up` | Apply all pending migrations |
| `npm run migrate:down` | Roll back the last applied migration |
| `npm run migrate:status` | Show applied vs pending migrations |

### Example

```sql
-- add_user_bio.sql (up)
ALTER TABLE users ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS bio VARCHAR(2000);

-- add_user_bio.down.sql (rollback)
ALTER TABLE users DROP COLUMN IF EXISTS bio;
```

## Schema Rules

- All tables use `snake_case` names (mapped via `@@map`)
- All columns use `snake_case` (mapped via `@map`)
- Model fields use `camelCase` in TypeScript
- All domain entities have `created_at` and `updated_at` timestamps
- All foreign keys use `ON DELETE CASCADE`
- Do NOT rename existing database tables or columns
- Do NOT drop or recreate tables without explicit approval

## Prisma Client Usage

```typescript
// ✅ Use the injected PrismaService
constructor(private readonly prisma: PrismaService) {}

// ✅ Select only the fields you need for DTOs
const user = await this.prisma.user.findUnique({
  where: { id },
  select: { id: true, firstName: true, email: true },
});

// ❌ Don't import PrismaClient directly
import { PrismaClient } from '../generated/prisma/client';
```

## Prisma 7 Import Path

Import types from the generated client (note the `/client` suffix):

```typescript
// ✅ Correct — use /client path
import type { User, Match } from '../generated/prisma/client';

// ❌ Wrong — this path doesn't resolve
import { User } from '../generated/prisma';
```

## Seeding

Seed scripts live in `prisma/seed.ts`. Run with `npx tsx prisma/seed.ts`. Seeds should use `upsert` to be idempotent.
